'''釋迦'''（{{lang-sa|शाक्य|Śākya}}；{{lang-pi|Sākiya}}、{{IAST|Sakka}}或{{IAST|Sakya}}<ref>Per J. F. Fleet, "The Inscription on the Piprawa Vase", ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=ZZLPO-SD_ecC&pg=PA164&lpg=PA164&dq=sakya+sakiya+sakka Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZZLPO-SD_ecC&pg=PA164&lpg=PA164&dq=sakya+sakiya+sakka |date=20190630191630 }}'', in Pāli, "Sākiya" is used primarily to refer to people of Shakya in general; "Sakka", primarily to the Shakya country as well as to its noble families; and "Sakya", primarily to members of the Buddhist order.</ref>） ，是[[古印度|古印度]]的一個{{en-link|系族|gotra}}的名稱，“釋迦”的字面意思為“大能”、“能”<ref>{{cite book|last1=Chandra Das|first1=Sarat|title=A Tibetan-English Dictionary: With Sanskrit Synonyms|date=1997|publisher=Asian Educational Services|location=New Delhi|isbn=81-206-0455-5|page=582}}</ref>。釋迦族主要出現在佛教文獻記載之中，「佛陀」[[釋迦牟尼|釋迦牟尼]]即是釋迦族人，釋迦族參與了佛陀[[入滅|入滅]]後的八王分[[舍利|舍利]]。

現代學界一般認為，釋迦族約在西元前一千年出現，原是居住地位於古印度東部、接近今[[尼泊爾|尼泊爾]]地方的一個小[[部落|部落]]；西元前6世紀至5世紀間，釋迦族形成自己的小型[[城邦|城邦]][[共和國|共和國]]（{{IAST|Śākya Gaṇarājya}}）<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Groeger|last2= Trenkler|first1=Herbert|first2=Luigi|year=2005|title="Zen and systemic therapy: Similarities, distinctions, possible contributions of Zen theory and Zen practice to systemic therapy."|url=http://www.jugendberatung.at/download/kunden/00009162.pdf|journal=Brief Strategic and Systematic Therapy European Review|volume=2|pages=2|via=}}</ref>，為[[寡頭政治|寡頭政治]]體制{{refn|group=note|name=Oligarchy|See:
* Gyan Swarup Gupta, Jayant Gadkari and the Encyclopedia Britannica use the term oligarchy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/India/Early-Vedic-period#ref485188|title=India - Early Vedic period|last=|first=|date=|website=Encyclopedia Britannica|access-date=March 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=India From Indus Valley Civilisation to Mauryas|last=Gupta|first=Gyan Swarup|publisher=South Asia Books|year=1999|isbn=978-8170227632|location=|pages=183}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Society and Religion | last=Gadkari |first=Jayant |publisher=South Asia Books |year=1996|isbn=978-8171547432|location=|pages=101}}</ref>
* Stephen Batchelor refers to Shakya (using the alternative spelling of Sakiya) as "a proud oligarchic republic."<ref>{{Cite book|title=After Buddhism|url=https://archive.org/details/afterbuddhismret0000batc|last=Batchelor|first=Stephen|publisher=Yale University Press|year=2015|isbn=978-0-300-20518-3|location=|pages=Chapter 2, Section 2, 8th Paragraph}}</ref>
* Kurt Spellmeyer: "The best word, then, to describe the Shakyas’ government might not be 'republic' at all. 'Oligarchy' may be a more accurate choice: rule by the elite."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tricycle.org/magazine/is-the-dharma-democratic/|title=Is the Dharma Democratic?|last=Spellmeyer|first=Kurt|date=Spring 2017|website=Tricycle Magazine|access-date=March 18, 2017|archive-date=2017-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201031253/https://tricycle.org/magazine/is-the-dharma-democratic/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
* Pankaj Mishra: "the Buddha was most likely not a prince, but a member of a republican oligarchy."<ref>{{Cite book|title=An End to Suffering: The Buddha in the World|last=Mishra|first=Pankaj|publisher=Farrar, Straus and Giroux|year=2010|pages=153}}</ref>
* Kenneth Pletcher, specifically referring to Shakya and other named states: "the fact that representation in these latter states' assemblies was limited to members of the ruling clan makes the term oligarchy, or even chiefdom, preferable."<ref>{{Cite book|title=The History of India|url=https://archive.org/details/historyofindia0000unse|last=Pletcher|first=Kenneth|publisher=Rosen Education Service|year=2010|isbn=978-1615301225|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/historyofindia0000unse/page/64 64]}}</ref>}}，由議會及其推選出的[[拉者|王者]]統治<ref>Gombrich, 1988, pp. 49-50</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=After Buddhism: Rethinking the Dharma for a Secular Age|url=https://archive.org/details/afterbuddhismret0000batc|last=Batchelor|first=Stephen|publisher=Yale University Press|year=2015|isbn=978-0300205183|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/afterbuddhismret0000batc/page/37 37]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Historical Buddha|last=Schumann|first=H.W.|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass|year=2016 |edition =New |isbn=978-8120818170|location=|pages=17–18}}</ref><ref>Hirakawa, 2007, p. 21</ref>，都城設於[[迦毘羅衛城|迦毘羅衛城]]，依附於[[憍薩羅國|憍薩羅國]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Long Discourses of the Buddha: A Translation of the Digha Nikaya|url=https://archive.org/details/longdiscoursesbu00wals|last=Walshe|first=Maurice|publisher=Wisdom Publications|year=1995|isbn=0-86171-103-3|location=http://lirs.ru/lib/sutra/Long_Discourses_of_the_Buddha(Digha_Nikaya).Walshe.pdf|pages=[https://archive.org/details/longdiscoursesbu00wals/page/n205 409]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=After Buddhism|url=https://archive.org/details/afterbuddhismret0000batc|last=Batchelor|first=Stephen|publisher=Yale University Press|year=2015|isbn=978-0-300-20518-3|location=|pages=Chapter 2, Section 2, 7th paragraph}}</ref> ，佛陀在世時迦毘羅衛城為[[毘琉璃王|毘琉璃王]]所滅<ref>Raychaudhuri H. (1972). ''Political History of Ancient India'', Calcutta: University of Calcutta, pp.177-8</ref><ref>Kosambi D.D. (1988). ''The Culture and Civilisation of Ancient India in Historical Outline'', New Delhi: Vikas Publishing House, {{ISBN|0-7069-4200-0}}, pp.128-9</ref>。此外，現代[[尼瓦尔人|尼瓦尔人]]的金匠有因釋迦牟尼賜姓而自稱是釋迦族。

另有一種說法是，亞洲北部的游牧民族，古波斯與古希臘稱其為[[斯基泰人|斯基泰人]]，釋迦族為其一支，又稱[[塞迦|塞迦]]，原分佈在裏海鹹海以北，西元前七世紀因戰亂向西移動，東部釋迦族逃往西藏變成[[小月氏|小月氏]]，西部釋迦族沿鹹海東側南下，其中一部份崇拜太陽神的日族在西元前六世紀遷移到恆河上游以東，最後在拉布迪河上游定居，釋迦牟尼出身於此。

==文獻記載==
釋迦族屬於[[剎帝利|剎帝利]][[种姓制度|種姓]]，自稱為[[印度|印度]][[甘蔗王|甘蔗王]]（即Ikshvaku，[[巴利文|巴利文]]：okkāka）<ref>《法苑珠林》卷八：「《菩薩本行經》-{云}-，甘蔗王次前有王，名大茅草。即以王位付諸大臣，大眾圍繞，送王出城。剃除鬚髮，服出家衣。……成就四禪，具足五通，得成王仙。……有一獵師，游行山野，遙見王仙，謂是白鳥，遂即射之。……爾時彼地有兩滴血，即便生出二甘蔗牙，漸漸高大。至時，甘蔗熟，日炙開剖，其一莖蔗出一童子，更一莖蔗出一童女。……此童子者，既是日炙熟甘蔗，開而出生故，一名善生。又其從甘蔗出故，第二復名甘蔗生。又以日炙甘蔗出故，亦名日種。彼女因緣一種無異，故名善賢，復名水波。時彼諸臣取甘蔗種所生童子，小年時即灌其頂立以為王。其賢善女，至年長大堪能伏事，即拜為王第一之妃。」釋迦族的起源，又可見《長阿含經》及《佛祖統記》。</ref>的後裔，源自古代傳說的[[太阳王朝|太阳王朝]]<ref name="law">Law, BC. (1973). ''Tribes in Ancient India'', Bhandarkar Oriental Series No.4, Poona: Bhandarkar Oriental Research Institute, pp. 245–56.</ref>。釋迦族自稱為日種（{{IAST|Ādicca nāma gottena}}）<ref>{{Cite book|title=Gotama Buddha: A Biography Based on the Most Reliable Texts, Volume 1|last=Nakamura|first=Hajime|publisher=Kosei Publishing Company|year=2000|isbn=978-4333018932|location=|pages=124}}</ref><ref>Batchelor, 2015, Chapter 2, section 2, paragraph 2</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Group of Discourses (Sutta Nipata)|last=Norman|first=K.R.|publisher=Pali Text Society at Oxford|year=2001|isbn=0860133036|location=http://www.ahandfulofleaves.org/documents/SuttaNipata_Norman_1997-2001.pdf|pages=51}}</ref>，即以[[太陽|太陽]]為崇拜對象<ref>{{Cite book|title=Living Buddha: An Interpretive Biography|last=Ikeda|first=Daisaku|publisher=Middleway Press|year=2012|isbn=978-0-9779245-2-3|location=|pages=6}}</ref><ref>Batchelor, 2015, Chapter 2, section 1, paragraph 10</ref> 。釋迦族以瞿曇為姓氏<ref>《翻译名义集》卷一：“瞿昙，或憍昙弥，或俱谭。西域记云：乔达摩，旧云瞿昙，讹略也。古翻甘蔗、泥土等。南山曰：非也。瞿昙，星名，从星立称。至于后代，改姓释迦。慈恩云：释迦之群望也。文句曰：瞿昙，此云纯淑，应法师翻为‘地最胜’，谓除天外，人类中此族最胜。”</ref>，巴利聖典將釋迦族的瞿曇譜系追溯至[[鸯耆罗仙人|鸯耆罗仙人]]<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Nt4nbp1VIhsC|title=The Indian Encyclopaedia: Gautami Ganga -Himmat Bahadur|date=2002|publisher=Cosmo Publication|isbn=81-7755-257-0|edition=Volume 9|location=New Delhi|page=2677|last1=Ganga|last2=Bahadur|first1=Gautami|first2=Himmat|editor=Subodh Kapoor|access-date=2018-11-07|archive-date=2019-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190630191630/https://books.google.com/books?id=Nt4nbp1VIhsC|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Edward J. Thomas, ''The Life of Buddha'' p. 22</ref>，佛經中將遵守[[雅利亞|聖]]法律之[[補特伽羅_(佛教)|人]]稱為[[雅利安人|雅利安人]]（ariya-puggala）。

